{
  "stem": "3022.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I always believed that my great-grandfather's blessing was the tsinnah-- was the protective shield over me in, in, in even the worst situations.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We-- as I started to tell you, I went to the leadership camp on the Romanian border.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Before I went to the camp, months before that, I informed my father that I will go to the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my father said, agreed, OK.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But when the time came, because of he needed my help in the business, he refused my leaving, and we had a falling out.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I left anyhow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I never came back home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I stayed in Cracow, got a job, and went to work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Four weeks later, the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "On September-- Friday morning of September 1, I was in the apartment of my uncle when the first Stuka planes flew over Cracow and dropped the bombs.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And next to us was-- were barracks of Polish soldiers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the first time that I saw dead and wounded being carried out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And somehow from that day on, my world was never the same.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That Friday we saw dog fights over the city of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Several Polish biplanes would get up in the air and try to fight the German fighters very unsuccessfully.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There was a atmosphere of distrust.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The Poles started accusing Jews of being spies for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "A stranger that walked into a strange neighborhood would, would, would be accosted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "All of a sudden, we found out that although for, for-- we lived in Poland for 10 centuries, we were never considered equal citizens.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "On Sunday, my mother came.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
